other_tests.findings: Gallbladder appears under distended with multiple gallstones and no gallbladder wall thickening or pericholecystic fluid to suggest acute cholecystitis. The common bile duct is of normal caliber as well as the intrahepatic biliary ducts. There is no choledocholithiasis. Liver shows unremarkable contours with scattered millimetric hepatic cysts or hematomas.
